            "dcterms:format": "application/ld+json",
            "dcterms:type": "Ontology"
          },
          "role": "Territory-Space measurement (ASFID basis)",
          "usage": "M2 tensor formulas use ASFID dimensions (A, S, F, I, D)"
        },
        "sphinxEye": {
          "@id": "m3sphinx:SphinxEye",
          "rdfs:seeAlso": "https://github.com/Echopraxium/tscg/blob/main/ontology/M3_Sphinx_Eye.jsonld",
          "dcterms:documentation": {
            "@id": "https://github.com/Echopraxium/tscg/blob/main/ontology/M3_Sphinx_Eye.jsonld",
            "dcterms:format": "application/ld+json",
            "dcterms:type": "Ontology"
          },
          "role": "Map-Space interpretation (ORIVE basis - PROPOSED)",
          "usage": "Future: M2 GenericConcepts may have ORIVE characterization for Map quality"
        }
      },
      "rdfs:seeAlso": "https://github.com/Echopraxium/tscg/blob/main/ontology/docs/TSCG_M2_GenericConcepts_Ontology_README.md",
      "dcterms:documentation": {
        "@id": "https://github.com/Echopraxium/tscg/blob/main/ontology/docs/TSCG_M2_GenericConcepts_Ontology_README.md",
        "dcterms:format": "text/markdown",
        "dcterms:type": "Documentation"
      },
      "rdfs:comment": "M2 layer constructs GenericConcepts through tensorization of M3 ASFID dimensions from Eagle Eye (Territory-Space). Bicephalous architecture: Eagle Eye measures phenomena (ASFID), Sphinx Eye interprets models (ORIVE proposed). Each GenericConcept is characterized by its tensor formula, category, epistemic gap, and polarity.",
      "m2:tensorSpace": "T_M2 = ГѓВўГ…В Гўв‚¬Вў_{k=1}^3 (H_M3)^ГѓВўГ…В Гўв‚¬вЂќk",
      "m2:totalComponents": 155,
      "m2:componentBreakdown": {
        "order1": 5,
        "order2": 25,
        "order3": 125
      },
      "m2:epistemicGapFormula": "ГѓЕЅГўв‚¬ВќГѓЕЅГ‹Е“(M) = ГѓВўГўвЂљВ¬Гўв‚¬вЂњP(Reality) - ModelГѓВўГўвЂљВ¬Гўв‚¬вЂњ ГѓВўГ‹вЂ Г‹вЂ  [0,1]",
      "m2:polarityPrinciple": "N-ary polarity framework: neutral (N=1), dual (N=2), ternary (N=3), quaternary (N=4), pentagonal (N=5), or general N-ary (N>5). Binary dual is most common case but not exclusive. Polarity describes intrinsic multiplicity of GenericConcept manifestation.",
      "m2:categoryTheory": {
        "m2:functor_tensorization": "F_ГѓВўГ…В Гўв‚¬вЂќ: Cat_M3 ГѓВўГўв‚¬В Гўв‚¬в„ў Cat_M2",
        "m2:functor_instantiation": "F_instantiate: Cat_M2 ГѓВўГўв‚¬В Гўв‚¬в„ў Cat_M1",
        "m2:morphism_inclusion": "ГѓВўГ…В Гўв‚¬В  (e.g., Homeostasis ГѓВўГ…В Гўв‚¬В  Regulation)",
        "m2:morphism_composition": "ГѓВўГ‹вЂ Г‹Е“ (e.g., Learning = Memory ГѓВўГ‹вЂ Г‹Е“ Adaptation)",
        "m2:morphism_duality": "op (e.g., Divergence = Convergence^op)",
        "m2:morphism_emergence": "ГѓВўГўв‚¬ВЎГўв‚¬Лњ (multiple ГѓВўГўв‚¬В Гўв‚¬в„ў emergent)"
      },
      "m2:criticalDecisions": {
        "m2:time_external": "Time is parameter in M3, not 6th dimension. Temporal GenericConcepts (Memory, Process) require integration ГѓВўГўв‚¬В Гўв‚¬в„ў M2",
        "m2:memory_is_m2": "M(t) = ГѓВўГ‹вЂ Г‚В«(D-F)dГѓВЏГўв‚¬Еѕ requires temporal integration, hence M2 not M3",
        "m2:regulation_is_m2": "AГѓВўГ…В Гўв‚¬вЂќSГѓВўГ…В Гўв‚¬вЂќF coupling required, hence M2 not M3",
        "m2:flow_is_m3": "F is 3rd dimension with axiom FГѓВўГўв‚¬В°Г‚ВҐ0.1, not M2 GenericConcept",
        "m2:axes_removed_v8": "Triple axes framework (Model/Reality, Analytical/Constructive, Composition/Decomposition) removed. Replaced by: Map-Territory distinction documented as theoretical foundation (see TSCG_Map_Territory_Theoretical_Foundation.md). Composition/Decomposition promoted to dual GenericConcepts.",
        "m2:nary_polarity_adopted_v13": "N-ary polarity framework adopted in v13.0.0. Replaces binary restriction. Polarity represents intrinsic multiplicity: neutral (N=1), dual (N=2), ternary (N=3), quaternary (N=4), pentagonal (N=5), N-ary (N>5). Examples: Switch (N-ary states), Mode (N-ary operational categories), Polarity GenericConcept itself (N-ary value poles).",
        "m2:purity_principle": "M2 uses pure vocabulary (Ontology, Systems Theory, Cybernetics) - no domain-specific terms. Domain concepts belong to M1 extensions."
      },
