        "Social network structure patterns - sociology",
        "Topological invariants (genus, Euler characteristic) - mathematics"
      ],
      "m2:distinctionNote": "Topology classifies structures by connectivity properties (model-theoretic abstraction), while Network represents concrete structural instances (reality-theoretic). Structure (M3) is the raw arrangement, Topology extracts its invariant equivalence class.",
